procedures.name: Blood Sampling
procedures.label: Blood Draw
procedures.description: Collection of blood samples for pharmacokinetic (PK), pharmacodynamic (PD), and clinical safety laboratory assessments (serum chemistry, hematology, coagulation).

code.decode: Collection of venous blood by venipuncture

procedures.name: Urine Collection
procedures.label: Urine Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of urine samples, including 24-hour pooled samples, for measurement of copper and molybdenum content, urinalysis, drug screening, and pregnancy testing.

procedures.name: Fecal Collection
procedures.label: Fecal Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of individual fecal samples for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Physical Examination
procedures.label: Physical Exam
procedures.description: A full or symptom-driven physical examination including assessments of the cardiovascular, respiratory, gastrointestinal, and neurological systems.

procedures.name: Vital Signs Measurement
procedures.label: Vital Signs
procedures.description: Assessment of body temperature, heart rate, respiratory rate, and systolic and diastolic blood pressure.

procedures.name: 12-lead Electrocardiogram
procedures.label: ECG
procedures.description: Triplicate 12-lead ECG to assess heart rate, intervals (PR, QRS, QT and QTc), and other clinically significant findings.

procedures.name: Oral Administration of Study Intervention
procedures.label: Drug Administration
procedures.description: Oral administration of ALXN1840 tablets with 240 mL of water after an overnight fast.

procedures.name: Pregnancy Test
procedures.label: Pregnancy Test
procedures.description: Urine or serum pregnancy testing for females of childbearing potential.

procedures.name: Urine Drug Screen
procedures.label: Drug Screen
procedures.description: Screening for drugs of abuse via urine sample at screening and check-in.

procedures.name: Alcohol Test
procedures.label: Alcohol Test
procedures.description: Testing for alcohol consumption at screening and check-in.

procedures.name: Infectious Disease Screening
procedures.label: HIV/Hep B/C Screen
procedures.description: Screening for Human Immunodeficiency Virus (HIV), Hepatitis B, and Hepatitis C.

procedures.name: Cannula Placement
procedures.label: Cannula Placement
procedures.description: Placement of a cannula to minimize needle sticks for repeated blood draws.

procedures.name: Height and Weight Measurement
procedures.label: Anthropometry
procedures.description: Measurement of height, weight, and calculation of Body Mass Index (BMI).

procedures.name: Food and Fluid Sample Collection
procedures.label: Dietary Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of samples from all meal and fluid batches for analysis of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Inductively Coupled Plasma Mass Spectrometry
procedures.label: ICP-MS Analysis
procedures.description: Laboratory analysis to determine the copper and molybdenum concentration of intake (food, fluids) and output (urine, feces) samples.

medicalDevices.name: Cannula
medicalDevices.label: Venous Cannula
medicalDevices.description: A cannula may be placed to minimize needle sticks for repeated blood draws.

medicalDevices.name: Catheter
medicalDevices.label: Venous Catheter
medicalDevices.description: A catheter may be used for venous access, not to be left in place for longer than 72 hours.

medicalDevices.name: Automated Blood Pressure Device
medicalDevices.label: Automated BP Device
medicalDevices.description: Completely automated device for assessing blood pressure and heart rate measurements.

medicalDevices.name: Inductively Coupled Plasma Mass Spectrometer
medicalDevices.label: ICP-MS
medicalDevices.description: Instrument used to determine the copper and molybdenum concentration of various biological and dietary samples.
